<section id="sect-00010">
<title>Foodborne Diseases</title>
<para id="para-00026">Within the United States, <term class="no-emphasis" id="term-00025">foodborne illness</term> is fairly common, with an estimated one out of every six individuals becoming ill from contaminated food or drinks and approximately 3,000 deaths related to foodborne illnesses each year (CDC, 2022b). <link target-id="table-00005" document="m00169"/> describes the top pathogens responsible for foodborne illnesses and death.</para>
