<caption>A bull’s-eye rash (erythema migrans) is often a characteristic sign of Lyme disease. (credit: CDC, Public Domain)</caption>
</figure>
<figure class="scaled-down" id="fig-00002"><media alt="A bullseye-shaped rash spreads over a person's shoulder. It is dark in the center and fades subtly as it expands out."><image mime-type="image/jpg" src="../../media/PH_Figure_13_02_005.jpg"/></media>
